transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, my name is David Rommel, R-O-M-M-E-L.

Speaker 1: I placed an order with you guys last week and just received it yesterday or the day before,

Speaker 2: I'm not exactly sure, just within the last couple of days I received it.

Speaker 1: And I believe I got the wrong prescription.

Speaker 2: Sure, I can take a look to see what's going on.

Speaker 1: What's your last name and a zip code, sir?

Speaker 2: R-O-M-M-E-L, and my zip code is 33983.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I do see here on my system that they sent out the Viagra AGB,

Speaker 2: however, what does the marking on the pill say on yours?

Speaker 1: Okay, hold on, let me get one out.

Speaker 2: Oh, let's see, it's so little, hold on a second,

Speaker 1: yeah, it's not what it used to be, just like everything else.

Speaker 2: Marking on the pill is 340.

Speaker 1: Got it.

Speaker 2: So with that info, I can confirm that they made a mistake on your order.

Speaker 1: The only marking you should have seen is 100 on the pill.

Speaker 2: I'm going to notify the pharmacy and then we're going to go ahead and ship a new order out for you.

Speaker 1: Okay, now, let's make sure we're talking about the right thing,

Speaker 2: because the reason I called was for that score blue.

Speaker 1: We only carry two, though, so you're going to get the correct one.

Speaker 2: So the score blue is what they're going to send me, correct?

Speaker 1: Yeah, correct.

Speaker 2: That one is going to have 100 engraved on the pill.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect.

Speaker 2: I thought this was the same as I've already got, so I said, well, something went wrong here.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no problem, sir.

Speaker 2: You can hold on to the ones you have, keep them or dispose of them, but we'll send you the correct one.

Speaker 1: Perfect.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: That was too easy.

Speaker 2: I didn't expect it to be this easy.

Speaker 1: No problem, sir.

Speaker 2: Pharmacy sometimes makes a mistake when the machine that dispenses it kind of mixes,

Speaker 1: but we'll send you the right one.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: I appreciate your help.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Yep, thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye.
